  "prompt": "What language do babies think in?",
  "response": "Babies don't think in language in the same way adults do. Their early thinking is pre-linguistic and based more on sensory experiences, emotions, and basic cognition. Before developing language skills, babies:\n\n1. Think in sensations and feelings\n2. Use visual and sensory processing\n3. Develop understanding through experiences\n4. Recognize patterns and emotional responses\n\nAs they grow and learn language, their thinking gradually becomes more structured and verbal. The specific language they eventually think in depends on the language(s) they are exposed to during early development.",
